21InterpolationType GetNonAuxiliaryInterpolationType(InterpolationType interpolation)
22{
23 return (interpolation == INTERPOLATION_CENTROID ? INTERPOLATION_SMOOTH : interpolation);
24}
25} // namespace
26// The ES 3.0 spec is not clear on this point, but the ES 3.1 spec, and discussion
27// on Khronos.org, clarifies that a smooth/flat mismatch produces a link error,
28// but auxiliary qualifier mismatch (centroid) does not.
29bool InterpolationTypesMatch(InterpolationType a, InterpolationType b)
30{
31 return (GetNonAuxiliaryInterpolationType(a) == GetNonAuxiliaryInterpolationType(b));
32}

113bool ShaderVariable::operator==(const ShaderVariable &other) const
114{
115 if (type != other.type || precision != other.precision || name != other.name ||
116 mappedName != other.mappedName || arraySizes != other.arraySizes ||
117 staticUse != other.staticUse || active != other.active ||
118 fields.size() != other.fields.size() || structName != other.structName ||
119 isRowMajorLayout != other.isRowMajorLayout || location != other.location ||
120 binding != other.binding || imageUnitFormat != other.imageUnitFormat ||
121 offset != other.offset || readonly != other.readonly || writeonly != other.writeonly ||
122 index != other.index || interpolation != other.interpolation ||
123 isInvariant != other.isInvariant || texelFetchStaticUse != other.texelFetchStaticUse)
124 {
125 return false;
126 }
127 for (size_t ii = 0; ii < fields.size(); ++ii)
128 {
129 if (fields[ii] != other.fields[ii])
130 return false;
131 }
132 return true;
133}

135void ShaderVariable::setArraySize(unsigned int size)
136{
137 arraySizes.clear();
138 if (size != 0)
139 {
140 arraySizes.push_back(size);
141 }
142}
143
144unsigned int ShaderVariable::getInnerArraySizeProduct() const
145{
146 unsigned int arraySizeProduct = 1u;
147 for (size_t idx = 1; idx < arraySizes.size(); ++idx)
148 {
149 arraySizeProduct *= getNestedArraySize(static_cast<unsigned int>(idx));
150 }
151 return arraySizeProduct;
152}
153
154unsigned int ShaderVariable::getArraySizeProduct() const
155{
156 return gl::ArraySizeProduct(arraySizes);
157}
158
159void ShaderVariable::indexIntoArray(unsigned int arrayIndex)
160{
161 ASSERT(isArray());
162 flattenedOffsetInParentArrays = arrayIndex + getOutermostArraySize() * parentArrayIndex();
163 arraySizes.pop_back();
164}
165
166unsigned int ShaderVariable::getNestedArraySize(unsigned int arrayNestingIndex) const
167{
168 ASSERT(arraySizes.size() > arrayNestingIndex);
169 unsigned int arraySize = arraySizes[arraySizes.size() - 1u - arrayNestingIndex];
170
171 if (arraySize == 0)
172 {
173 // Unsized array, so give it at least 1 entry
174 arraySize = 1;
175 }
176
177 return arraySize;
178}
179
180unsigned int ShaderVariable::getBasicTypeElementCount() const
181{
182 // GLES 3.1 Nov 2016 section 7.3.1.1 page 77 specifies that a separate entry should be generated
183 // for each array element when dealing with an array of arrays or an array of structs.
184 ASSERT(!isArrayOfArrays());
185 ASSERT(!isStruct() || !isArray());
186
187 // GLES 3.1 Nov 2016 page 82.
188 if (isArray())
189 {
190 return getOutermostArraySize();
191 }
192 return 1u;
193}
194
195unsigned int ShaderVariable::getExternalSize() const
196{
197 unsigned int memorySize = 0;
198
199 if (isStruct())
200 {
201 // Have a structure, need to compute the structure size.
202 for (const auto &field : fields)
203 {
204 memorySize += field.getExternalSize();
205 }
206 }
207 else
208 {
209 memorySize += gl::VariableExternalSize(type);
210 }
211
212 // multiply by array size to get total memory size of this variable / struct.
213 memorySize *= getArraySizeProduct();
214
215 return memorySize;
216}

218bool ShaderVariable::findInfoByMappedName(const std::string &mappedFullName,
219 const ShaderVariable **leafVar,
220 std::string *originalFullName) const
221{
222 ASSERT(leafVar && originalFullName);
223 // There are three cases:
224 // 1) the top variable is of struct type;
225 // 2) the top variable is an array;
226 // 3) otherwise.
227 size_t pos = mappedFullName.find_first_of(".[");
228
229 if (pos == std::string::npos)
230 {
231 // Case 3.
232 if (mappedFullName != this->mappedName)
233 return false;
234 *originalFullName = this->name;
235 *leafVar = this;
236 return true;
237 }
238 else
239 {
240 std::string topName = mappedFullName.substr(0, pos);
241 if (topName != this->mappedName)
242 return false;
243 std::string originalName = this->name;
244 std::string remaining;
245 if (mappedFullName[pos] == '[')
246 {
247 // Case 2.
248 size_t closePos = mappedFullName.find_first_of(']');
249 if (closePos < pos || closePos == std::string::npos)
250 return false;
251 // Append '[index]'.
252 originalName += mappedFullName.substr(pos, closePos - pos + 1);
253 if (closePos + 1 == mappedFullName.size())
254 {
255 *originalFullName = originalName;
256 *leafVar = this;
257 return true;
258 }
259 else
260 {
261 // In the form of 'a[0].b', so after ']', '.' is expected.
262 if (mappedFullName[closePos + 1] != '.')
263 return false;
264 remaining = mappedFullName.substr(closePos + 2); // Skip "]."
265 }
266 }
267 else
268 {
269 // Case 1.
270 remaining = mappedFullName.substr(pos + 1); // Skip "."
271 }
272 for (size_t ii = 0; ii < this->fields.size(); ++ii)
273 {
274 const ShaderVariable *fieldVar = nullptr;
275 std::string originalFieldName;
276 bool found = fields[ii].findInfoByMappedName(remaining, &fieldVar, &originalFieldName);
277 if (found)
278 {
279 *originalFullName = originalName + "." + originalFieldName;
280 *leafVar = fieldVar;
281 return true;
282 }
283 }
284 return false;
285 }
286}
287
288const sh::ShaderVariable *ShaderVariable::findField(const std::string &fullName,
289 uint32_t *fieldIndexOut) const
290{
291 if (fields.empty())
292 {
293 return nullptr;
294 }
295 size_t pos = fullName.find_first_of(".");
296 if (pos == std::string::npos)
297 {
298 return nullptr;
299 }
300 std::string topName = fullName.substr(0, pos);
301 if (topName != name)
302 {
303 return nullptr;
304 }
305 std::string fieldName = fullName.substr(pos + 1);
306 if (fieldName.empty())
307 {
308 return nullptr;
309 }
310 for (size_t field = 0; field < fields.size(); ++field)
311 {
312 if (fields[field].name == fieldName)
313 {
314 *fieldIndexOut = static_cast<GLuint>(field);
315 return &fields[field];
316 }
317 }
318 return nullptr;
319}

321bool ShaderVariable::isBuiltIn() const
322{
323 return (name.size() >= 4 && name[0] == 'g' && name[1] == 'l' && name[2] == '_');
324}
325
326bool ShaderVariable::isEmulatedBuiltIn() const
327{
328 return isBuiltIn() && name != mappedName;
329}
330
331bool ShaderVariable::isSameVariableAtLinkTime(const ShaderVariable &other,
332 bool matchPrecision,
333 bool matchName) const
334{
335 if (type != other.type)
336 return false;
337 if (matchPrecision && precision != other.precision)
338 return false;
339 if (matchName && name != other.name)
340 return false;
341 ASSERT(!matchName || mappedName == other.mappedName);
342 if (arraySizes != other.arraySizes)
343 return false;
344 if (isRowMajorLayout != other.isRowMajorLayout)
345 return false;
346 if (fields.size() != other.fields.size())
347 return false;
348
349 // [OpenGL ES 3.1 SPEC Chapter 7.4.1]
350 // Variables declared as structures are considered to match in type if and only if structure
351 // members match in name, type, qualification, and declaration order.
352 for (size_t ii = 0; ii < fields.size(); ++ii)
353 {
354 if (!fields[ii].isSameVariableAtLinkTime(other.fields[ii], matchPrecision, true))
355 {
356 return false;
357 }
358 }
359 if (structName != other.structName)
360 return false;
361 return true;
362}
363
364bool ShaderVariable::isSameUniformAtLinkTime(const ShaderVariable &other) const
365{
366 // Enforce a consistent match.
367 // https://cvs.khronos.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=16261
368 if (binding != -1 && other.binding != -1 && binding != other.binding)
369 {
370 return false;
371 }
372 if (imageUnitFormat != other.imageUnitFormat)
373 {
374 return false;
375 }
376 if (location != -1 && other.location != -1 && location != other.location)
377 {
378 return false;
379 }
380 if (offset != other.offset)
381 {
382 return false;
383 }
384 if (readonly != other.readonly || writeonly != other.writeonly)
385 {
386 return false;
387 }
388 return ShaderVariable::isSameVariableAtLinkTime(other, true, true);
389}
390
391bool ShaderVariable::isSameInterfaceBlockFieldAtLinkTime(const ShaderVariable &other) const
392{
393 return (ShaderVariable::isSameVariableAtLinkTime(other, true, true));
394}
395
396bool ShaderVariable::isSameVaryingAtLinkTime(const ShaderVariable &other) const
397{
398 return isSameVaryingAtLinkTime(other, 100);
399}
400
401bool ShaderVariable::isSameVaryingAtLinkTime(const ShaderVariable &other, int shaderVersion) const
402{
403 return (ShaderVariable::isSameVariableAtLinkTime(other, false, false) &&
404 InterpolationTypesMatch(interpolation, other.interpolation) &&
405 (shaderVersion >= 300 || isInvariant == other.isInvariant) &&
406 (location == other.location) &&
407 (name == other.name || (shaderVersion >= 310 && location >= 0)));
408}

452std::string InterfaceBlock::fieldPrefix() const
453{
454 return instanceName.empty() ? "" : name;
455}
456
457std::string InterfaceBlock::fieldMappedPrefix() const
458{
459 return instanceName.empty() ? "" : mappedName;
460}
461
462bool InterfaceBlock::isSameInterfaceBlockAtLinkTime(const InterfaceBlock &other) const
463{
464 if (name != other.name || mappedName != other.mappedName || arraySize != other.arraySize ||
465 layout != other.layout || isRowMajorLayout != other.isRowMajorLayout ||
466 binding != other.binding || blockType != other.blockType ||
467 fields.size() != other.fields.size())
468 {
469 return false;
470 }
471
472 for (size_t fieldIndex = 0; fieldIndex < fields.size(); ++fieldIndex)
473 {
474 if (!fields[fieldIndex].isSameInterfaceBlockFieldAtLinkTime(other.fields[fieldIndex]))
475 {
476 return false;
477 }
478 }
479
480 return true;
481}

488void WorkGroupSize::fill(int fillValue)
489{
490 localSizeQualifiers[0] = fillValue;
491 localSizeQualifiers[1] = fillValue;
492 localSizeQualifiers[2] = fillValue;
493}
494
495void WorkGroupSize::setLocalSize(int localSizeX, int localSizeY, int localSizeZ)
496{
497 localSizeQualifiers[0] = localSizeX;
498 localSizeQualifiers[1] = localSizeY;
499 localSizeQualifiers[2] = localSizeZ;
500}
501
502// check that if one of them is less than 1, then all of them are.
503// Or if one is positive, then all of them are positive.
504bool WorkGroupSize::isLocalSizeValid() const
505{
506 return (
507 (localSizeQualifiers[0] < 1 && localSizeQualifiers[1] < 1 && localSizeQualifiers[2] < 1) ||
508 (localSizeQualifiers[0] > 0 && localSizeQualifiers[1] > 0 && localSizeQualifiers[2] > 0));
509}
510
511bool WorkGroupSize::isAnyValueSet() const
512{
513 return localSizeQualifiers[0] > 0 || localSizeQualifiers[1] > 0 || localSizeQualifiers[2] > 0;
514}
515
516bool WorkGroupSize::isDeclared() const
517{
518 bool localSizeDeclared = localSizeQualifiers[0] > 0;
519 ASSERT(isLocalSizeValid());
520 return localSizeDeclared;
521}
522
523bool WorkGroupSize::isWorkGroupSizeMatching(const WorkGroupSize &right) const
524{
525 for (size_t i = 0u; i < size(); ++i)
526 {
527 bool result = (localSizeQualifiers[i] == right.localSizeQualifiers[i] ||
528 (localSizeQualifiers[i] == 1 && right.localSizeQualifiers[i] == -1) ||
529 (localSizeQualifiers[i] == -1 && right.localSizeQualifiers[i] == 1));
530 if (!result)
531 {
532 return false;
533 }
534 }
535 return true;
536}
537
538int &WorkGroupSize::operator[](size_t index)
539{
540 ASSERT(index < size());
541 return localSizeQualifiers[index];
542}
543
544int WorkGroupSize::operator[](size_t index) const
545{
546 ASSERT(index < size());
547 return localSizeQualifiers[index];
548}
549
550size_t WorkGroupSize::size() const
551{
552 return 3u;
553}
